snippet.title: Jack Fowler
snippet.description:
Jack Fowler was introduced to music by his St Helenian father, and soul and reggae music were a permanent fixture in his household. Performing from a young age, Jack seemed to always find himself in front of a camera, singing along to his father’s favourites: Stevie Wonder, James Brown and The Spinners. As Jack hit his teen years, he developed his own eclectic taste, specifically favouring the R&B, rap, house and garage genres with his passion for music quickly becoming part of his foundation. In 2011 Jack discovered J. Cole and was inspired by his ability to bring his music to life through storytelling, depicting relatable R&B themes accompanied by a hip-hop baseline. Self-titled PartyNextDoor’s album in 2013 became Jack’s summer soundtrack, and this is where he began his writing journey.

– A glimpse into the life of Jack Fowler.
